1
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:07,458
[suspenseful music]

2
00:00:07,458 --> 00:00:08,625
Milkit!

3
00:00:08,833 --> 00:00:09,708
Where are you?

4
00:00:09,916 --> 00:00:11,208
Can you hear me?

5
00:00:11,416 --> 00:00:12,208
Milkit!

6
00:00:12,416 --> 00:00:13,291
Milkit!

7
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:14,750
I'll find you.

8
00:00:16,833 --> 00:00:18,041
[SATILS]
Milkit.

9
00:00:20,750 --> 00:00:22,416
Milkit.

10
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:27,000
Come now.

11
00:00:27,208 --> 00:00:28,500
Rise and shine.

12
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:35,208
Oh, no, but how?

13
00:00:35,416 --> 00:00:38,000
Oh, my, someone's
learned some new tricks.

14
00:00:38,208 --> 00:00:40,208
That reaction you gave
me just now almost

15
00:00:40,208 --> 00:00:41,916
seemed genuinely human.

16
00:00:42,125 --> 00:00:43,500
You've done well.

17
00:00:43,708 --> 00:00:45,166
I'm proud of you.

18
00:00:45,375 --> 00:00:46,208
Stop.

19
00:00:46,416 --> 00:00:47,916
I want my master.

20
00:00:50,208 --> 00:00:52,041
Well, that's too bad.

21
00:00:52,041 --> 00:00:56,166
I had this playroom specially
made in a secret location.

22
00:00:56,375 --> 00:00:58,916
Nobody's coming to save you.

23
00:00:59,125 --> 00:01:01,166
Foolish girl, you're
never going to see

24
00:01:01,166 --> 00:01:03,416
that master of yours again.

25
00:01:03,625 --> 00:01:05,916
All that's left for you
to do is writhe in pain

26
00:01:06,125 --> 00:01:07,333
as I carve you up.

27
00:01:07,541 --> 00:01:10,166
You'll be even
uglier than before.

28
00:01:10,166 --> 00:01:13,333
Now, be a good girl
and entertain me

29
00:01:13,333 --> 00:01:15,416
with your sheer agony.

30
00:01:15,625 --> 00:01:19,625
I'd do anything for my
master, but that's not you.

31
00:01:20,833 --> 00:01:23,458
[whip cracks]

32
00:01:24,625 --> 00:01:26,291
Insolent slave!

33
00:01:26,500 --> 00:01:28,333
How dare you speak back to me?

34
00:01:28,333 --> 00:01:30,875
You have no right
to choose your owner.

35
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:37,750
Hey, Flum.

36
00:01:37,958 --> 00:01:39,458
Welcy?

37
00:01:39,458 --> 00:01:42,291
Did you settle things with
the church's newest lapdog?

38
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:43,708
How'd you know?

39
00:01:43,916 --> 00:01:44,875
Dein came in here.

40
00:01:44,875 --> 00:01:47,041
And not long after, so did you.

41
00:01:47,250 --> 00:01:48,916
The most logical
inference is that you

42
00:01:49,125 --> 00:01:50,416
might have been following him.

43
00:01:50,625 --> 00:01:51,458
OK.

44
00:01:51,458 --> 00:01:52,416
What about you?

45
00:01:52,625 --> 00:01:53,791
Why are you here?

46
00:01:53,791 --> 00:01:55,333
I heard that this
mansion recently had

47
00:01:55,541 --> 00:01:56,875
a secret chamber installed.

48
00:01:56,875 --> 00:01:58,333
I'm here to investigate.

49
00:01:58,541 --> 00:01:59,625
A secret chamber?

50
00:01:59,833 --> 00:02:00,875
Where is it?

51
00:02:01,083 --> 00:02:02,166
I need you to take me there.

52
00:02:02,375 --> 00:02:03,791
It's urgent!

53
00:02:03,791 --> 00:02:07,041
Ink and Milkit could be
in grave danger as we speak.

54
00:02:07,041 --> 00:02:08,625
Sure,
I'll help, no problem.

55
00:02:08,833 --> 00:02:10,000
This way.

56
00:02:12,166 --> 00:02:14,750
It won't be long
now, Milkit and Ink.

57
00:02:14,958 --> 00:02:15,750
Please wait.

58
00:02:15,958 --> 00:02:17,458
I'm coming.

59
00:02:23,208 --> 00:02:25,166
[SATILS]
That other girl you call master

60
00:02:25,375 --> 00:02:28,041
is a hopeless idiot,
wasting her time trying

61
00:02:28,041 --> 00:02:30,041
to fix your worthless face.

62
00:02:30,041 --> 00:02:32,416
[GASP] Ink's here?

63
00:02:32,625 --> 00:02:35,041
Only for me to ruin it again.

64
00:02:35,250 --> 00:02:36,750
Let's pull off
those bandages,

65
00:02:36,750 --> 00:02:39,041
so I can get
a better look at it.

66
00:02:39,250 --> 00:02:42,333
Hey, what?

67
00:02:42,333 --> 00:02:45,416
Demonstrating how loyal
you are to your master?

68
00:02:45,625 --> 00:02:46,750
How precious.

69
00:02:49,125 --> 00:02:50,375
Look below.

70
00:02:51,583 --> 00:02:54,708
Take even one step back
and you'll fall off.

71
00:02:54,916 --> 00:02:58,291
Behold the fate you'll
suffer if that should happen.

72
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:01,291
And if you're stubborn
enough to survive that--

73
00:03:02,916 --> 00:03:06,500
[growling]

74
00:03:09,583 --> 00:03:11,458
--your new friends
there will be waiting

75
00:03:11,458 --> 00:03:13,583
patiently to eat you alive.

76
00:03:13,583 --> 00:03:16,166
Go on, make your choice.

77
00:03:16,375 --> 00:03:19,333
Whoa, it looks like
you're about to slip,

78
00:03:19,541 --> 00:03:21,625
or maybe those chains will
come loose from the wall

79
00:03:21,833 --> 00:03:23,875
and decide for you.

80
00:03:24,083 --> 00:03:26,166
Whatever will you do?

81
00:03:31,625 --> 00:03:33,750
You'd sacrifice
your body just to keep

82
00:03:33,958 --> 00:03:35,583
hiding that precious face?

83
00:03:35,791 --> 00:03:38,875
I'm shocked you value a promise
with her more than your life.

84
00:03:39,083 --> 00:03:41,291
It's so sweet, I could cry.

85
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:43,833
Master, please come save me.

86
00:03:44,041 --> 00:03:47,458
[SATILS] Wow, praying for
your new master to rescue you?

87
00:03:47,666 --> 00:03:49,833
You're a slave, remember?

88
00:03:50,041 --> 00:03:51,458
You can be louder than that.

89
00:03:51,666 --> 00:03:54,166
Scream and cry for me.

90
00:03:54,166 --> 00:03:57,333
Oh, so defiant.

91
00:03:57,541 --> 00:04:00,750
The old you never reacted
to anything-- your only flaw,

92
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:02,708
but an annoying one.

93
00:04:02,916 --> 00:04:04,125
Very good.

94
00:04:04,125 --> 00:04:07,291
I'm liking your new
impertinent spirit.

95
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:10,000
Crushing it will be a treat.

96
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:12,958
[scream]

97
00:04:16,041 --> 00:04:17,583
[FLUM]
Why can't you get angry at me

98
00:04:17,583 --> 00:04:20,750
for not showing up
to protect you sooner?

99
00:04:20,958 --> 00:04:23,166
Let me have it.

100
00:04:23,166 --> 00:04:25,458
We're not slave and master.

101
00:04:25,458 --> 00:04:27,166
You're Milkit, and I'm Flum.

102
00:04:27,166 --> 00:04:29,875
That's all there is.

103
00:04:29,875 --> 00:04:31,125
[NARRATOR]
In that moment--

104
00:04:31,333 --> 00:04:32,916
Better start moving.

105
00:04:32,916 --> 00:04:35,875
You won't like it when my knife
pokes through your body over

106
00:04:36,083 --> 00:04:37,458
and over again.

107
00:04:37,666 --> 00:04:40,000
[NARRATOR] --she decided
to believe in her master

108
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:43,458
until the bitter end
and go down fighting.

109
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,000
Such a look in your eye.

110
00:04:47,208 --> 00:04:49,166
Fine then, have it your way.

111
00:04:49,166 --> 00:04:51,333
Resist and have
your body shredded up

112
00:04:51,541 --> 00:04:53,500
and scarred from head to toe.

113
00:04:53,708 --> 00:04:57,291
[evil laugh]

114
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:04,291
[explosion]

115
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:05,583
Huh?

116
00:05:09,708 --> 00:05:13,875
You witch, leave
my Milkit alone!

117
00:05:13,875 --> 00:05:15,416
Who the hell are you?

118
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,291
Now you'll pay.

119
00:05:25,916 --> 00:05:27,125
You'll pay!

120
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:28,166
You'll pay!

121
00:05:28,375 --> 00:05:29,583
You'll pay!

122
00:05:31,416 --> 00:05:35,875
You deserve to suffer for this.

123
00:05:36,083 --> 00:05:38,208
[MILKIT]
My master.

124
00:05:41,333 --> 00:05:43,750
I'm so sorry, my Milkit.

125
00:05:43,958 --> 00:05:45,708
I should have been here sooner.

126
00:05:53,416 --> 00:05:54,916
My dear Milkit.

127
00:05:57,583 --> 00:05:59,208
My dear master.

128
00:06:08,916 --> 00:06:10,291
I'm sorry.

129
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:12,208
I'm sorry, Ink.

130
00:06:12,416 --> 00:06:16,291
Truly, I said
such awful things.

131
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:17,708
I feel terrible.

132
00:06:17,708 --> 00:06:18,916
And I'm--

133
00:06:19,125 --> 00:06:24,000
[INK] Flum, why are
you apologizing?

134
00:06:25,708 --> 00:06:29,208
[FLUM] Because you're
a very dear friend to me.

135
00:06:29,416 --> 00:06:32,000
And yet I was so mean to you.

136
00:06:32,208 --> 00:06:35,583
And even after all that,
you stopped those eyeballs.

137
00:06:35,791 --> 00:06:38,041
You protected me when
I fought with Dein.

138
00:06:39,166 --> 00:06:41,125
Flum.

139
00:06:41,125 --> 00:06:43,000
Thank you, Ink.

140
00:06:44,166 --> 00:06:46,500
Oh, what's this?

141
00:06:46,708 --> 00:06:50,625
[screaming]

142
00:06:51,833 --> 00:06:53,166
[thud]

143
00:06:53,375 --> 00:06:56,000
[groaning]

144
00:07:00,125 --> 00:07:01,208
No, don't!

145
00:07:01,416 --> 00:07:02,833
You monsters!

146
00:07:03,041 --> 00:07:05,000
Get away from me!

147
00:07:05,208 --> 00:07:07,875
[screams]

148
00:07:18,166 --> 00:07:21,750
There, master, that's
the one who kidnapped me.

149
00:07:21,958 --> 00:07:25,416
Girl, I just did what
Satils asked me to.

150
00:07:25,625 --> 00:07:27,125
Sadly, both she
and that Dein guy

151
00:07:27,333 --> 00:07:29,125
turned out to be
good for nothings.

152
00:07:29,125 --> 00:07:30,458
Just pathetic.

153
00:07:30,666 --> 00:07:32,250
[FLUM]
I see.

154
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:34,750
So you were the one who made
Ink believe she was a burden.

155
00:07:34,958 --> 00:07:35,875
It's true.

156
00:07:36,083 --> 00:07:37,291
Why shouldn't she believe it?

157
00:07:37,291 --> 00:07:38,458
[MOTHER]
Nekt.

158
00:07:38,666 --> 00:07:40,875
Greetings, ladies.

159
00:07:41,083 --> 00:07:42,875
Please call me "Mother."

160
00:07:43,083 --> 00:07:46,333
You must be the renowned
Flum Apricot.

161
00:07:46,541 --> 00:07:48,458
[FLUM]
You're Mother.

162
00:07:48,666 --> 00:07:51,041
My, what chilly reception.

163
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:54,708
Anyhow, I hear you've
been looking after Ink.

164
00:07:54,708 --> 00:07:57,416
I owe you my gratitude.

165
00:07:57,416 --> 00:07:59,416
Thank you, dear.

166
00:07:59,416 --> 00:08:01,041
Shut the hell up.

167
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:04,250
You're no Mother, not after
everything you've done to Ink.

168
00:08:04,458 --> 00:08:06,000
Whatever do you mean?

169
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:09,166
Could you be referring to the
core Ink's heart once was?

170
00:08:09,375 --> 00:08:11,208
It's the same
for the other ones too.

171
00:08:11,416 --> 00:08:14,916
All my children have had their
hearts replaced with cores.

172
00:08:16,166 --> 00:08:19,208
But unlike the rest of us,
she's a useless failure.

173
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:23,833
Flum and the others I've
met since I ran away never

174
00:08:23,833 --> 00:08:25,291
hurt me or call me names.

175
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:27,583
They treat me well
and say I'm their friend.

176
00:08:27,791 --> 00:08:28,541
Oh, Ink.

177
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:30,291
You tell them.

178
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:32,125
Have you made some
friends during your

179
00:08:32,333 --> 00:08:33,875
unapproved escapades?

180
00:08:33,875 --> 00:08:38,041
Well, that's fine, but you
know that family comes first.

181
00:08:38,250 --> 00:08:41,125
Come, it's time we go home.

182
00:08:41,125 --> 00:08:43,000
[FLUM]
Don't do it, Ink!

183
00:08:44,416 --> 00:08:50,166
You and the rest,
you're not my family.

184
00:08:50,375 --> 00:08:52,125
[MOTHER]
Of course we are.

185
00:08:52,125 --> 00:08:55,000
I figured it
out after I left.

186
00:08:55,208 --> 00:08:58,833
The life I was forced to endure
and your world was all wrong

187
00:08:58,833 --> 00:09:02,416
because I met Flum and my
friends that made me truly

188
00:09:02,625 --> 00:09:04,416
laugh for the first time.

189
00:09:04,416 --> 00:09:07,750
And that's how I even
learned what laughing was.

190
00:09:07,958 --> 00:09:10,208
That's why I want
to always be with them.

191
00:09:12,416 --> 00:09:14,041
They're my friends
who care about me.

192
00:09:14,250 --> 00:09:16,875
And they're much more
important than your family.

193
00:09:17,083 --> 00:09:18,708
[MOTHER] You can't be
stupid enough to believe you

194
00:09:18,916 --> 00:09:21,458
could live together
with humans, can you?

195
00:09:21,666 --> 00:09:23,125
Did your time out
there cause you

196
00:09:23,125 --> 00:09:26,833
to forget you're a creepy,
eyeball-spitting monster?

197
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:29,541
How will you survive
without your medicine?

198
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:31,708
[FLUM] You don't care
about Ink's feelings.

199
00:09:31,916 --> 00:09:34,625
You're nothing
but a narcissistic monster!

200
00:09:37,666 --> 00:09:43,416
[INK] I'm happy here,
so I'm staying with them.

201
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:47,208
[MOTHER] Very well, I guess
your siblings were right.

202
00:09:47,416 --> 00:09:49,333
You're not needed.

203
00:09:52,416 --> 00:09:54,625
When you eventually
realize I was right,

204
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:56,875
you'll come to regret
this decision,

205
00:09:57,083 --> 00:10:00,291
you ungrateful, good
for nothing brat.

206
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:01,375
Are you OK?

207
00:10:01,583 --> 00:10:02,750
Enough!

208
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:04,500
And you dare call
yourself a "mother?"

209
00:10:04,708 --> 00:10:07,375
That's my mother, and you
can't speak to her like that.

210
00:10:07,583 --> 00:10:09,000
You're making me upset.

211
00:10:09,208 --> 00:10:10,708
Let's not get carried away.

212
00:10:10,916 --> 00:10:12,833
I haven't decided whether
we should kill this girl

213
00:10:12,833 --> 00:10:15,833
or make use of
the abilities she possesses.

214
00:10:15,833 --> 00:10:18,333
And she was able
to destroy a core, right?

215
00:10:18,541 --> 00:10:21,166
I'm rather intrigued
by this power of yours

216
00:10:21,375 --> 00:10:24,458
as research material,
I should say.

217
00:10:24,666 --> 00:10:26,708
Well, till next time.

218
00:10:26,916 --> 00:10:28,833
It's been fun.

219
00:10:29,041 --> 00:10:30,833
You won't get away!

220
00:10:33,916 --> 00:10:35,833
[INK]
It's all right, Flum.

221
00:10:35,833 --> 00:10:37,333
Thank you.

222
00:10:37,541 --> 00:10:41,166
But they-- they're the ones
who messed up your body.

223
00:10:41,375 --> 00:10:43,166
But you let me
be your friend.

224
00:10:43,375 --> 00:10:45,125
That was more
than enough for me.

225
00:10:45,333 --> 00:10:46,833
I'm happy.

226
00:10:47,041 --> 00:10:49,208
But we should end things.

227
00:10:49,416 --> 00:10:50,250
End?

228
00:10:50,458 --> 00:10:51,500
Mm-hmm.

229
00:10:52,375 --> 00:10:53,833
It's time.

230
00:10:53,833 --> 00:10:58,250
I'll embrace
a human life and death.

231
00:10:58,458 --> 00:10:59,500
Hold on.

232
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:01,250
Why are you
talking about death?

233
00:11:01,458 --> 00:11:03,000
It's my fault, isn't it?

234
00:11:03,208 --> 00:11:05,166
Sara and Eterna are gone.

235
00:11:06,583 --> 00:11:09,708
If we continue living
together like we did before,

236
00:11:09,916 --> 00:11:13,125
I could attack you
or Milkit without meaning to.

237
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:16,500
You might get hurt, or worse--

238
00:11:16,708 --> 00:11:20,458
I don't want to make any more
of my precious friends suffer.

239
00:11:20,666 --> 00:11:24,166
That's why I should die.

240
00:11:24,375 --> 00:11:27,125
Please, Flum, you're
the only one with the ability

241
00:11:27,333 --> 00:11:28,625
to break the core
that's been placed

242
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:30,541
where my heart should be.

243
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:33,583
You can, right?

244
00:11:33,791 --> 00:11:35,625
Please do it.

245
00:11:38,708 --> 00:11:41,166
If you'll do this
favor for me,

246
00:11:41,375 --> 00:11:44,250
I'll get to die as a normal
girl who had friends.

247
00:11:45,458 --> 00:11:47,000
No, I can't.

248
00:11:50,875 --> 00:11:52,416
I can't do it.

249
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:57,625
[MILKIT] And is that
really what you want?

250
00:11:57,833 --> 00:11:59,083
I think not.

251
00:12:01,041 --> 00:12:05,125
Not long ago, I felt
just the same as you.

252
00:12:05,333 --> 00:12:07,833
I was stuck in a dark
place I couldn't escape,

253
00:12:08,041 --> 00:12:12,333
ready to die, with no hope
that help was coming.

254
00:12:12,541 --> 00:12:17,250
But then I met my master,
and I started to change.

255
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:20,750
Isn't that why you
stayed with us?

256
00:12:20,958 --> 00:12:23,875
Aren't you trying to change
your life for the better?

257
00:12:24,083 --> 00:12:25,625
I am.

258
00:12:25,625 --> 00:12:28,666
I want to keep eating, bathing,
and relaxing with you all.

259
00:12:28,875 --> 00:12:30,833
Life just started getting fun.

260
00:12:33,375 --> 00:12:35,875
I want you to have
more of that.

261
00:12:36,083 --> 00:12:37,833
So then, what do we do?

262
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:41,333
That's right.

263
00:12:41,541 --> 00:12:43,458
Eterna would know.

264
00:12:43,666 --> 00:12:46,125
But I still don't
know if she's alive.

265
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:48,708
[footsteps]

266
00:12:48,916 --> 00:12:50,000
Over here.

267
00:12:52,083 --> 00:12:54,125
You holding up
all right, Flum?

268
00:12:54,333 --> 00:12:55,625
Gadhio!

269
00:12:55,625 --> 00:12:57,333
[GADHIO] It's good
to see you're still well.

270
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:00,458
I'm glad you're all OK.

271
00:13:00,666 --> 00:13:01,958
Same goes for you.

272
00:13:02,166 --> 00:13:03,625
How are you unscathed?

273
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:06,791
You think eyeballs
could stop me?

274
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:10,750
Eterna,
I'm sorry for everything.

275
00:13:10,958 --> 00:13:13,666
You've done nothing
that requires an apology.

276
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:21,916
Infuriating.

277
00:13:22,125 --> 00:13:23,625
I knew Jean was
on a power trip,

278
00:13:23,625 --> 00:13:26,583
but I never imagined he'd
go so far behind our backs.

279
00:13:26,791 --> 00:13:29,125
I don't want to sound
like I'm thankful to him,

280
00:13:29,333 --> 00:13:31,458
but in a strange way,
he led me to Milkit.

281
00:13:37,125 --> 00:13:39,666
Anyway, what'd I miss before
you caught up to us down there,

282
00:13:39,875 --> 00:13:41,000
Gadhio?

283
00:13:41,208 --> 00:13:42,750
You fought Nekt, right?

284
00:13:42,958 --> 00:13:45,166
I take it that one went right?

285
00:13:45,375 --> 00:13:47,250
Unfortunately,
the kid got away,

286
00:13:47,458 --> 00:13:49,958
vanished as soon as
it was clear I won.

287
00:13:50,166 --> 00:13:51,958
That was when Eterna
showed her face.

288
00:13:52,166 --> 00:13:53,083
Oh, right.

289
00:13:53,291 --> 00:13:55,375
I saw that Nekt had a bruise.

290
00:13:55,583 --> 00:13:57,583
And what's happened to you
since the last time we met up,

291
00:13:57,791 --> 00:13:59,416
Eterna?

292
00:13:59,416 --> 00:14:03,083
[ETERNA] Milkit and I ran into
Dein when we went out shopping.

293
00:14:03,291 --> 00:14:05,666
I used water magic
to protect her

294
00:14:05,875 --> 00:14:09,083
and fled from
the swarm of eyeballs.

295
00:14:09,291 --> 00:14:10,375
But apparently,
those eyeballs

296
00:14:10,583 --> 00:14:12,458
didn't give chase for long.

297
00:14:12,666 --> 00:14:14,000
She was making her
way back to you

298
00:14:14,208 --> 00:14:16,333
when we ran into each other.

299
00:14:16,541 --> 00:14:19,916
Ink must have
subconsciously kept you safe.

300
00:14:20,125 --> 00:14:22,916
So after that, the two of you
went to come help us out?

301
00:14:23,125 --> 00:14:25,708
[GADHIO] I was doing everything
I could to track you down.

302
00:14:25,916 --> 00:14:28,625
And along the way,
I met that Welcy girl.

303
00:14:28,833 --> 00:14:31,291
[FLUM] And Sara,
you said she's alive.

304
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:32,958
How did you find that out?

305
00:14:33,166 --> 00:14:35,541
[GADHIO]
She was in the demon realm.

306
00:14:38,625 --> 00:14:41,500
Right before she was
attacked by eyeballs,

307
00:14:41,708 --> 00:14:43,791
Neigass appeared
and came to her aid.

308
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:46,708
[FLUM]
Neigass saved her?

309
00:14:46,916 --> 00:14:50,083
Sara must have
left an impression.

310
00:14:50,291 --> 00:14:51,750
Great.

311
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:54,041
Did you happen to see Ed
and Jonny in the demon realm?

312
00:14:54,250 --> 00:14:56,583
I'm not familiar.

313
00:14:56,791 --> 00:14:59,375
So that means only
Sara made it out alive.

314
00:14:59,583 --> 00:15:02,500
That explains why
the girl was so distressed,

315
00:15:02,708 --> 00:15:04,375
even though she was safe.

316
00:15:04,583 --> 00:15:06,125
[SARA]
I'm begging you.

317
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:09,250
I promise I'll pay you
back to save my friends.

318
00:15:09,458 --> 00:15:12,041
I've lost far too
many people I love.

319
00:15:12,250 --> 00:15:15,083
Please, no more.

320
00:15:15,291 --> 00:15:17,791
Even if this girl is
an illusion you've made,

321
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,708
your primary goal is still
to break up the heroes party,

322
00:15:20,916 --> 00:15:21,750
is it not?

323
00:15:21,958 --> 00:15:23,166
Explain.

324
00:15:23,375 --> 00:15:25,458
What can I say
to earn your trust?

325
00:15:25,666 --> 00:15:27,583
Telling me all the demons
know about Origin

326
00:15:27,791 --> 00:15:29,916
would be an excellent start.

327
00:15:30,125 --> 00:15:33,541
After that, she told me
our party's true purpose.

328
00:15:33,750 --> 00:15:35,666
Is it not to kill
all the demons?

329
00:15:35,875 --> 00:15:37,250
[GADHIO]
Nope.

330
00:15:37,458 --> 00:15:40,125
It's to undo
the seal on Origin.

331
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:44,958
In the beginning,
Origin was a man-made machine

332
00:15:45,166 --> 00:15:48,000
designed as an infinite
source of energy.

333
00:15:48,208 --> 00:15:50,666
It brought humanity
great prosperity.

334
00:15:50,875 --> 00:15:53,958
Of course, that era
of peace did not last long.

335
00:15:55,333 --> 00:15:59,000
Their minds corrupted by power
and the promise of wealth.

336
00:15:59,208 --> 00:16:05,416
Humanity fought in a
bloody war till none remained.

337
00:16:05,625 --> 00:16:07,458
As if rejecting that outcome,

338
00:16:07,666 --> 00:16:10,625
the world gave birth
to a new kind of humanity.

339
00:16:10,833 --> 00:16:15,041
Among them, some were
blessed with immense power.

340
00:16:15,250 --> 00:16:17,333
They were called "Heroes."

341
00:16:17,541 --> 00:16:20,583
Thanks to the first Hero,
Origin was sealed,

342
00:16:20,791 --> 00:16:24,208
and with it,
the root cause of all evil.

343
00:16:24,416 --> 00:16:27,125
[GADHIO] But the difference
between sealed and destroyed

344
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:29,375
is a seal can be undone.

345
00:16:29,583 --> 00:16:33,583
That's why the church summoned
us to subjugate the Demon Lord.

346
00:16:33,791 --> 00:16:37,208
They're merely using
the Hero's Party as a means

347
00:16:37,416 --> 00:16:39,583
to bring back Origin.

348
00:16:39,791 --> 00:16:43,000
The seal is at
the Demon Lord's castle.

349
00:16:43,208 --> 00:16:44,708
It's kept safe.

350
00:16:44,916 --> 00:16:47,750
They have been
defending it for eons now.

351
00:16:50,083 --> 00:16:53,333
Wait, Dein claimed his
power came from Origin.

352
00:16:53,541 --> 00:16:56,333
And he seemed strong
enough to back it up.

353
00:16:56,541 --> 00:16:58,666
Does that mean something
happened to the seal?

354
00:16:58,875 --> 00:17:01,083
Yeah, it seems
Origin's influence

355
00:17:01,291 --> 00:17:02,958
is beginning to leak out.

356
00:17:03,166 --> 00:17:06,083
That's why Neigass came
to our kingdom to investigate

357
00:17:06,291 --> 00:17:07,500
the cause of the leak.

358
00:17:07,708 --> 00:17:10,458
Oh, so that's why
she was in Anichidey.

359
00:17:10,666 --> 00:17:13,333
[GADHIO] You ask me,
from what the demon said,

360
00:17:13,541 --> 00:17:16,541
I think one
of them is a traitor.

361
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:19,625
When the demon attacks occurred
ten and eight years ago,

362
00:17:19,833 --> 00:17:21,750
they weren't
the ones in charge.

363
00:17:21,958 --> 00:17:23,708
The church was.

364
00:17:23,916 --> 00:17:26,875
Someone on the demon side
must have colluded with them.

365
00:17:28,125 --> 00:17:30,166
You know that
Sara girl you met?

366
00:17:30,375 --> 00:17:31,625
She survived one.

367
00:17:31,833 --> 00:17:33,000
What a coincidence.

368
00:17:33,208 --> 00:17:35,958
She's not the only
one we know of.

369
00:17:36,166 --> 00:17:37,666
[FLUM]
Maria, right?

370
00:17:38,791 --> 00:17:41,208
After the attacks,
five pregnant women were

371
00:17:41,416 --> 00:17:43,625
abducted who each gave birth.

372
00:17:43,833 --> 00:17:46,208
Those kids are now
called the Spiral Children.

373
00:17:46,416 --> 00:17:50,041
And they were given
to the church for research.

374
00:17:50,250 --> 00:17:52,500
[FLUM] Are you saying
those kids were--

375
00:17:52,708 --> 00:17:54,541
[GADHIO]
Yeah, most likely.

376
00:17:54,750 --> 00:17:57,000
They treated children
just like monsters.

377
00:17:57,208 --> 00:17:59,750
[GADHIO] Does that mean
you saw their monsters?

378
00:17:59,958 --> 00:18:03,791
Yeah, I fought
one some time ago.

379
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:07,333
I did too, alongside my wife.

380
00:18:07,541 --> 00:18:09,250
Wait, you're married?

381
00:18:09,458 --> 00:18:12,166
I was up until that
Chimera killed her.

382
00:18:12,375 --> 00:18:13,750
[GASP]

383
00:18:13,958 --> 00:18:16,625
[GADHIO] After that,
I joined the Hero's Party

384
00:18:16,833 --> 00:18:19,708
to find answers
on what happened

385
00:18:19,916 --> 00:18:22,625
and get revenge on
the ones who killed my wife.

386
00:18:22,833 --> 00:18:24,458
Awful.

387
00:18:24,458 --> 00:18:27,916
Do they care so little for the
lives of their fellow humans?

388
00:18:28,125 --> 00:18:29,666
[ETERNA]
Not just the church.

389
00:18:30,958 --> 00:18:33,291
This entire kingdom couldn't
care less whether those

390
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:35,458
who call it home, live or die.

391
00:18:35,666 --> 00:18:36,916
Eterna.

392
00:18:36,916 --> 00:18:39,791
[GADHIO] You sound like
you know something.

393
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,916
Because I'm basically
the same as Ink.

394
00:18:43,125 --> 00:18:45,458
But somehow I've
made it this far.

395
00:18:47,166 --> 00:18:50,916
So I'm sure Ink will be fine.

396
00:18:51,125 --> 00:18:55,041
[NARRATOR] After that, Ink
received a heart transplant.

397
00:18:55,250 --> 00:18:56,833
Flum destroyed the Core.

398
00:18:57,041 --> 00:19:00,083
And Eterna used her magic
to take Dein's heart

399
00:19:00,291 --> 00:19:03,458
and ensure Ink took to it.

400
00:19:06,541 --> 00:19:08,875
[JEAN]
You think you know me.

401
00:19:09,083 --> 00:19:11,166
Explain yourself.

402
00:19:11,375 --> 00:19:14,666
I know that you are
in search of power.

403
00:19:14,875 --> 00:19:17,416
And as a devout
member of the clergy,

404
00:19:17,625 --> 00:19:19,833
I will guide the lost lambs.

405
00:19:21,250 --> 00:19:23,458
Oh, you've
caught my interest.

406
00:19:23,666 --> 00:19:25,833
I'll give you that much credit.

407
00:19:26,041 --> 00:19:29,708
[MARIA] I gave one of these to
Cyrill, and now it's your turn.

408
00:19:29,916 --> 00:19:31,791
Did you now?

409
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,083
Intriguing.

410
00:19:36,625 --> 00:19:39,250
Flare meteorite!

411
00:19:41,333 --> 00:19:42,291
Ha!

412
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:44,500
Take my blue flame!

413
00:19:49,875 --> 00:19:51,416
Tricky move.

414
00:19:52,791 --> 00:19:54,708
Wait, this isn't fire.

415
00:19:54,916 --> 00:19:57,125
It is both fire
and ice at once.

416
00:19:59,125 --> 00:20:04,083
My power has finally ascended
past that of any mortal man.

417
00:20:04,291 --> 00:20:05,458
Well, that seems new.

418
00:20:05,666 --> 00:20:07,833
What could Jean be
up to this time?

419
00:20:08,041 --> 00:20:10,166
The lord's work.

420
00:20:10,375 --> 00:20:12,208
Wonder if I made
her mad there.

421
00:20:14,666 --> 00:20:16,083
You used it.

422
00:20:19,125 --> 00:20:23,666
Flum, tell me,
what should I do?

423
00:20:23,875 --> 00:20:27,125
He used some strange
magic I'd never seen before.

424
00:20:27,333 --> 00:20:28,750
What do you think
the odds are that they

425
00:20:28,958 --> 00:20:30,875
obtained Origin's power too?

426
00:20:31,083 --> 00:20:32,250
Impossible.

427
00:20:32,458 --> 00:20:33,916
How could they?

428
00:20:34,125 --> 00:20:36,583
We have the text
of the seal's formula.

429
00:20:36,791 --> 00:20:39,291
And it's kept
under lock and key.

430
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:43,666
Only I know where it is
and, of course, Dhiza.

431
00:20:43,875 --> 00:20:44,750
Good.

432
00:20:44,958 --> 00:20:46,458
You've returned to me.

433
00:20:46,666 --> 00:20:48,875
All that I do is
for you, after all.

434
00:20:49,083 --> 00:20:51,583
I was successful in tracking
down their hideout.

435
00:20:51,791 --> 00:20:56,125
The church has a research team
that we were not aware of.

436
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:59,833
The children,
Necromancy and Chimera's.

437
00:21:00,041 --> 00:21:01,000
That's enough.

438
00:21:01,208 --> 00:21:03,916
Please save your strength.

439
00:21:04,125 --> 00:21:05,250
How's it going?

440
00:21:05,458 --> 00:21:07,291
Not good.

441
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:09,000
Too little, too late.

442
00:21:09,208 --> 00:21:11,458
[NARRATOR]
Welcy uncovered
a great deal of evidence

443
00:21:11,666 --> 00:21:13,250
in Satils' mansion,

444
00:21:13,458 --> 00:21:16,041
leading her to the
church's research facility.

445
00:21:16,250 --> 00:21:19,416
But by then, they had already
cleared the place out.

446
00:21:20,916 --> 00:21:22,458
So they knew we were coming.

447
00:21:22,666 --> 00:21:24,541
I suppose that means
I need to keep any information

448
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:26,500
I find close to the chest.

449
00:21:32,583 --> 00:21:35,875
According to Origin, in order
to build his resistance

450
00:21:36,083 --> 00:21:37,458
to the power of reversal,

451
00:21:37,458 --> 00:21:40,750
we must absorb Flum Apricot
without killing her?

452
00:21:40,958 --> 00:21:43,625
That's awfully easy
for papa to say.

453
00:21:43,833 --> 00:21:47,541
Desperate times, the clock
is still ticking down on us.

454
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:51,666
I suspect one of your kin
of committing treason.

455
00:21:51,875 --> 00:21:52,833
Preposterous.

456
00:21:53,041 --> 00:21:54,291
We have our duty.

457
00:21:58,041 --> 00:21:59,250
Jonny.

458
00:21:59,458 --> 00:22:01,250
What's wrong, dear?

459
00:22:01,458 --> 00:22:05,250
It's all my fault.
They're gone forever.

460
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:09,416
You had a nightmare,
didn't you?

461
00:22:09,625 --> 00:22:10,708
I've got you now.

462
00:22:10,916 --> 00:22:12,583
It's all right.

463
00:22:12,791 --> 00:22:14,541
Wow, check it out!

464
00:22:14,750 --> 00:22:16,750
It's chow time.

465
00:22:16,958 --> 00:22:18,750
I want to dig in.

466
00:22:18,958 --> 00:22:21,208
It looks almost too
beautiful to mess up.

467
00:22:21,416 --> 00:22:23,458
I hope there's something
to each of your liking.

468
00:22:23,666 --> 00:22:25,916
These recipes were new to me.

469
00:22:26,125 --> 00:22:28,166
Give yourself some
credit, just for once.

470
00:22:28,375 --> 00:22:30,416
Your cooking's
always delicious.

471
00:22:30,625 --> 00:22:33,291
[ETERNA] Milkit, take what
Flum says with a grain of salt.

472
00:22:33,500 --> 00:22:35,875
You're her rock,
so she's biased.

473
00:22:36,083 --> 00:22:37,291
[GADHIO]
But, you know,

474
00:22:37,291 --> 00:22:39,333
compared to when
she was traveling with us,

475
00:22:39,541 --> 00:22:42,000
I'd say Milkit is good for her.

476
00:22:42,208 --> 00:22:44,250
Aww,
you're joining her, Gadhio?

477
00:22:44,458 --> 00:22:46,833
If I'm master's rock,
then she's mine as well.

478
00:22:47,041 --> 00:22:51,583
Honestly, I don't know if
I could go on without her.

479
00:22:51,791 --> 00:22:53,041
Really?

480
00:22:54,458 --> 00:22:57,750
Who knows what
tomorrow will bring?

481
00:22:57,958 --> 00:23:01,500
But for now,
I'm with my family.

482
00:23:05,416 --> 00:23:09,041
Hey, Milkit, I love you.

483
00:23:09,250 --> 00:23:10,541
And I love you.

484
00:23:13,208 --> 00:23:15,583
I'll live my life with them.

485
00:23:18,666 --> 00:23:20,500
[NARRATOR]
After a few days passed,

486
00:23:20,708 --> 00:23:23,416
the town felt
unusually peaceful.

487
00:23:23,625 --> 00:23:25,375
Another quiet morning.

488
00:23:25,583 --> 00:23:26,666
Oh.

489
00:23:27,416 --> 00:23:29,791
If it isn't
my favorite adventurer.

490
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:31,541
Have any new jobs come in?

491
00:23:31,750 --> 00:23:32,666
Wha-- Hold on.

492
00:23:32,875 --> 00:23:33,708
Seriously?

493
00:23:33,916 --> 00:23:35,791
Am I really your favorite?

494
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,833
I was just joking.

495
00:23:38,041 --> 00:23:39,208
You want work?

496
00:23:39,416 --> 00:23:43,000
Well, then,
how about this one?
